Read and prepare the data

Dataset: crp2.csv

Description: 120 patients admitted to intensive care (ICU) with sepsis. C-reactive protein (CRP) is a marker of inflammation and, potentially, a marker of sepsis resolution. CRP was measured over 6 days (crp1,â¦crp6) or until discharge/death (discharge_r).

Other variables:

  • SAPS - severity score measured within the first 24h in the ICU

  • age - age at admission

  • SEX - Male / Female

  • SEPSIS - category of sepsis (Sepsis/Severe Sepsis/Septic Shock)

  • antib_1h - was antibiotherapy administer within the first hour in ICU (No/Yes)

Changing the data structure wide to long

crp.Data <- pivot_longer(data = crp.Data.wide, 
                         cols = c(crp1, crp2, crp3, crp4, crp5, crp6), #cols = crp1:crp6 
                         names_to = "day", 
                         names_transform = list(day = as.numeric), #day as number 
                         values_to = "crp", 
                         names_prefix = "crp", 
                         values_drop_na=TRUE)

Plotting the predicted values from the random intercept model with the GEE model

ggplot(crp.Data, aes(x=day, y = predict(reffect), group=ID)) + 
  geom_line(alpha=.5) +  
  labs(title="CRP in sepsis patients in ICU",
       x = "Time (days)",
       y = "logCRP") + 
  theme_bw() + 
  geom_line(aes(y=predict(gee.exch), group="none"),
          color="blue", lwd=2)

Exercises

Dataset

Dataset: HIVmetabolites.csv

Description: Neurocognitive decline of chronically infected HIV.

Variables: - patid - patient id

  • sexbin - male == 1

  • racebin - white == 1

  • educbin - educ>12 == 1

  • age - age in years

  • cd4val - cd4 count at enrollment

  • nadircd4 - lifetime nadir CD4 count

  • durationHIV - duration of HIV infection (years)

  • HAART_years - years on HAART

  • cpescore - CNS meds penetration score

  • placopy.val - copy number of HIV RNA

  • ADCstage.fac2b - impairment status (impaired == 1)

  • GDS - Global Deficit Score

  • t - years since enrollment (continuous)

  • time.cat - years since enrollment (categorical)

  • abs_* - absolute metabolite levels in 3 brain regions

  • rel_* - relative (to Cr) metabolite levels in 3 brain regions

  • rel_mid2 - Mid-frontal Cho/Cr ratio

hiv.met <- read.csv("https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/1sra63885g2rudu8locj6/HIVmetabolites.csv?rlkey=wutk5tddu1qdzn0nx0j571ylv&st=3gj0bu3u&dl=1")
